## Customization
### Styling:
Customize styles by editing css/JekyllTwilight.css. The theme uses CSS custom properties for easy adjustments.

### Social Icons:
Social icons are provided as SVGs (found in images/social/). You can update the colors and hover effects in the CSS.

### Includes and Layouts:
The themeâ€™s structure is modular. Update or create new includes in _includes/ and layouts in _layouts/ to suit your content needs.

### Portfolio Filtering:
Portfolio items are filtered via JavaScript in JekyllTwilight.js. Ensure each project item in your portfolio has a class (e.g., wordpress, snippets, video) and a corresponding data-categories attribute for filtering.

## Usage
### Update Content:

Create new blog posts in _posts/.
Modify pages using the layouts provided in _layouts/.
Deploy:
After testing locally with jekyll serve, deploy your site to GitHub Pages by pushing the repository to your GitHub account. The theme is optimized for GitHub Pages.

